    "plan_content": "The plan is complete and saved to `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/rippling-growing-rose.md`. Here's a summary of what I found and what the plan covers:\n\n---\n\n## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Plan Summary\n\n### What I explored\nI read the full source of **IRC**, **Nostr**, and the **Plugin SDK** (`src/plugin-sdk/core.ts`) to understand every file and pattern needed. PulseBoard closely follows these existing plugins.\n\n### 16 new files to create (all under `extensions/pulseboard/`)\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard` with `openclaw.channel` metadata block |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | Manifest (`id: pulseboard`, `channels: [pulseboard]`) |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` — main runtime entry |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry` — lightweight onboarding entry |\n| `api.ts` | Public barrel (accounts + setup surface) |\n| `runtime-api.ts` | Private runtime barrel (borrows from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`) |\n| `src/types.ts` | `PulseBoardAccountConfig`, `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardInboundMessage` |\n| `src/config-schema.ts` | Zod schemas (boards, dmPolicy, allowFrom, textChunkLimit) |\n| `src/accounts.ts` | `resolvePulseBoardAccount`, env-var fallbacks (`PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN`) |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore` |\n| `src/client.ts` | Fictional `fetch`-based HTTP client (`postToBoard`, `sendDm`) |\n| `src/send.ts` | `sendMessagePulseBoard` — routes to board post or DM |\n| `src/inbound.ts` | `dispatchPulseBoardInbound` — routes to DM or group dispatch |\n| `src/setup-surface.ts` | `ChannelSetupAdapter` + `ChannelSetupWizard` (token + username + dmPolicy) |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` — the full plugin with both DM + group support |\n| `src/channel.test.ts` | Vitest tests (meta, capabilities, config, outbound, pairing, security) |\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **`#board-name`** → group chat; plain username → direct message (mirrors IRC's `#channel` convention)\n- **`textChunkLimit: 4000`** — exactly as specified\n- **`chatTypes: [\"direct\", \"group\"]`** — full direct + board support\n- **`dmPolicy: \"pairing\"`** default — safest, matches IRC/Nostr\n- **No external npm dependencies** — fictional platform uses `fetch`\n- **Zero modifications to existing files**",
